Paper Code: ETMT-421 L T/P C
Paper: Waste and Heat Recovery Systems 3 1 4


UNIT- I
Waste Heat Recovery:
  Introduction - Principles of Thermodynamics and Second Law, Cogeneration system.
  Sources of waste heat and its potential applications, Waste heat survey and measurements, Data collection, Limitations and affecting factors Heat recovery equipment and systems.
[T1, T2, R1, R2]

UNIT- II
Waste Heat Recovery Systems:
  Introduction, classification and design of Recuperators, Regenerators, and economizers.
[T1, T2, R1, R2]

UNIT- III
Waste Heat Boilers:
  Classification, Location, Service Conditions, Design Considerations, Unfired combined Cycle, Supplementary fired combined cycle, fired combined cycle, Thermic fluid heaters.
[T1, T2, R1, R2]

UNIT- IV
Applications & Techno Economics of Waste Heat Recovery Systems:
  Applications in industries, selection of waste heat recovery technologies - financial considerations - operations and investment costs of waste heat recovery.
  Introduction to tri-generation and quad-generation.
[T1, T2, R1, R2]


